 among them that other cousin of Lydia’s, Ardalion’s brother Innocent, who, for some reason or another, got executed by the shooting squad soon after our departure. (To be frank, all this would be far more befitting at the beginning of the first chapter than at the beginning of the third.)

Bold and scoffing but inwardly tortured

(O, my soul, will your torch not ignite?),

From the porch of your God and His orchard

Why take off for the Earth and the night?



